42nd Street, at N.W. corner of Seventh Ave; showing reconstruction of the Rialto Theatre Building an early instance of the use of glass bricks as a building material.

September 26, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

"The New York Times", moved uptown to 42nd Street, in 1905, at the southern junction of Broadway and Seventh Ave., (commonly known as Times Square). It was housed in this building up to 1913, when an annex was required.

Gift of "The New York Times".
